---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout title="Academic | PoliceConduct.org" pagePath="/partner/academic/">
  <main class="flex-grow-1">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb mb-3">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item">
              <a class="link-dark" href="/partner/">Partners</a>
            </li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Academic</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-end">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">
              Value proposition
            </p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">Solving the Data Gap in Policing</h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              Structured ground-truth data for academic and research
              institutions.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Built for</div>
                <div class="fw-semibold">
                  Researchers and academic institutions
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted small">
                  Illuminate the dark matter of everyday police-citizen
                  interactions.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">
              1. Solving the dark matter of policing
            </h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
              The vast majority of police-citizen interactions never show up in
              official crime stats, yet they shape long-term trust and safety.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
              <li>
                Structured metadata for stops, frisks, and verbal warnings.
              </li>
              <li>Longitudinal datasets on pre-arrest conduct.</li>
              <li>
                Quantify the trust deficit between official reports and
                community experience.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Research pitch
                </div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Help quantify the gap between official statistics and
                  community-documented interactions using the first structured
                  dataset of pre-arrest conduct.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-light border-top border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          2. Standardizing pracademic collaboration
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Move beyond deploy-first, explain-later. Real-time data streams
          support rapid-cycle research and evidence-based oversight.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Real-time data streams
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Live lab research</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Test how transparency tools affect officer behavior with
                  actionable insights in months, not years.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Rapid-cycle analysis
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Policy briefs that matter</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Publish timely findings while departments can still implement
                  change.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">3. Academic and research benefits</h2>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-bordered align-middle">
            <thead class="table-light">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Researcher need</th>
                <th scope="col">PoliceConduct.org capability</th>
                <th scope="col">Impact on academic career</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Data authenticity</strong></td>
                <td
                  >Multi-source verification across video, reports, and records.</td
                >
                <td>Stronger confidence intervals and peer-review success.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Bias mitigation</strong></td>
                <td>Compare user reports to official demographic data.</td>
                <td>High-impact publications on bias and procedural justice.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Large-scale analysis</strong></td>
                <td>API access across multiple states.</td>
                <td>Cross-jurisdictional studies at scale.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Monell research</strong></td>
                <td>Track the moving force of municipal policy.</td>
                <td
                  >New legal-criminology frameworks for civil rights research.</td
                >
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-gray-100 border-top border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-start">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">4. Longitudinal study infrastructure</h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">
              We track officer professional trajectories across departments,
              enabling research on wandering officers and the effectiveness of
              retraining programs.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Longitudinal database
                </div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Permanent, immutable records support multi-year trend analysis
                  and grant work.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          5. Ethical governance and anonymization
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Provide de-identified datasets that meet Institutional Review Board
          requirements through data minimization and anonymization protocols.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div
          class="d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row align-items-lg-center justify-content-between gap-3"
        >
          <div>
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-1">Ready to partner on a grant?</h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">
              We can provide a letter of support for DOJ or NIJ grant
              applications.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            class="btn btn-dark rounded-0"
            href="/about/contact?whoami=Partner&message=I%27m%20interested%20in%20a%20letter%20of%20support%20for%20a%20research%20grant%20proposal."
          >
            Request a letter of support
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
